Title: Debugging Rules

Principles
- Reproduce before fixing. Add minimal failing case if needed.
- Prefer logs and narrow diffs over broad changes.
- Never suppress errors without handling root cause.

Checklist
- [ ] Confirm environment and versions
- [ ] Capture error and stack trace
- [ ] Identify last known good state
- [ ] Create hypothesis and test it
- [ ] Add/adjust tests and observability

Prompts
```text
Follow debugging.mdc:
- Reproduce, collect errors, form hypotheses, and validate.
- Propose minimal fix with acceptance criteria.
```

